07/02/2007
WASHINGTON, United States -- Talks in Washington between Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul and US officials focused on the fight against the Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK) terrorist organisation. 
He met on Tuesday (February 6th) with Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice, after talks Monday with Vice President Dick Cheney and National Security Adviser Stephen Hadley.
According to media reports, Gul also expresssed Turkish concerns to officials about the possible impact on bilateral ties should the US Congress pass a resolution condemning the mass killings of Armenians in the waning days of the Ottoman Empire as genocide.(Aksam, Zaman, NTV - 07/02/07; Turks.US, AP, AFP - 06/02/07)
